Description:
Several vulnerabilities were reported in Solaris. A remote user can modify data on the target system. A local user can cause denial of service conditions on the target system. A local user can modify data on the target system.
A local user can exploit a flaw in the Solaris Kernel Zones virtualized block driver component to modify data and cause denial of service conditions [CVE-2017-3276].

A remote user can exploit a flaw in the Solaris Kernel component to partially modify data [CVE-2016-8330].

A local user can exploit a flaw in the Solaris Kernel component to partially modify data [CVE-2017-3301].

